Lucky Star: You are born under a lucky star. Doctors say you are exceptionally healthy, and your family is overjoyed at your arrival. (+Luck, +Health)
Into Comfort: You open your eyes to a warm, wealthy home. Your future seems bright and full of potential. (+Wealth)
Genius Prodigy: The midwife remarks on your unusually alert gaze. You seem to observe the world with intense focus from the very first moment. (+IQ)
Cherished Child: You are welcomed with overwhelming love and tenderness. A deep sense of security surrounds you. (+LoveReceiving, +Mental Health)
Golden Touch: A birthmark deemed "lucky" by your elders. Your family believes fortune will follow you everywhere. (+Luck, +Wealth slightly)
Robust Beginning: You have a strong cry and perfect health scores. The doctors are impressed. (+Health)
Diplomat's Temperament: You are a calm, serene baby who rarely cries, instantly charming everyone you meet. (+EQ, +Look)
Heir to Legacy: Born into a family of renowned artists/scholars, great things are expected of you from day one. (+IQ)
Community Blessing: Your birth coincides with a local festival or good omen. The whole community celebrates you. (+Luck, +LoveReceiving)
Miracle Baby: Born against all odds after many struggles, you are a symbol of hope and are deeply cherished. (+LoveReceiving, +Mental Health)
Neutral / Mixed Start
Perfectly Average: You arrive without much fanfare. You are a healthy, normal baby to a normal family. A blank slate awaits.
Unexpected Guest: Your arrival was a surprise, but a welcome one. Your family scrambles to adapt, but love fills the home.
Stormy Entry: You are born during a powerful thunderstorm. Some say it's an omen—but of what? (Random small +/- to Luck)
Twin Dynamics: You share your birthday with a sibling. Your lives will be forever linked, for better or worse.
Crossroads Birth: Born at a hospital at the intersection of two cities. Your identity may always feel a bit divided.
The Observer: You are a quiet, watchful baby. You don't demand much, so some overlook you, but you see everything.
Fragile Start: You are born prematurely, small and requiring immediate medical care. The road ahead begins with a struggle. (-Health, -Wealth slightly from medical bills)
Unwanted Burden: Your birth is met with silence, not joy. The financial and emotional strain on the family is palpable. (-LoveReceiving, -Mental Health, -Wealth)
Omen of Misfortune: A superstitious elder claims your birth time is inauspicious, casting a shadow of doubt from the start. (-Luck, -LoveReceiving in family)
Struggle for Breath: A complicated delivery leaves you weak. Your first fight for survival is won, but at a cost. (-Health, parents' mental health affected)
Into Hardship: You are born into deep poverty. Your cradle is a cardboard box, your first lesson is scarcity. (-Wealth, -Health slightly)
Marked Difference: A visible birthmark or minor disfigurement leads to whispers and pitying looks from the start. (-Look, -Mental Health)
Orphaned Dawn: Tragedy strikes at your birth. You enter the world alone, handed to the care of the state. (-LoveReceiving, -Wealth, -Mental Health)
Family Curse: An old tale says firstborns in your family are doomed to bad luck. You are the firstborn. (-Luck)
Crisis Born: You arrive in the midst of a family crisis—bankruptcy, war, or natural disaster. You are a light in the darkness, but the darkness is very real. (-Wealth, -Health, +LoveReceiving from one parent)
The Replacement: You were born shortly after the loss of another child. You are loved, but also bear the weight of being a "substitute." (-Mental Health, +LoveReceiving but with pressure)
Sickly Seed: A congenital illness is diagnosed early. Your life will be a series of doctor visits and limitations. (-Health, -Wealth, -Luck slightly)
Taboo Child: Born under circumstances your culture deems shameful (e.g., out of wedlock, to forbidden love). Your very existence is considered a sin by some. (-LoveReceiving in society, -Mental Health)
Abandoned: Left on a doorstep or at an orphanage. Your first home is an institution, your name given by a stranger. (-LoveReceiving, -Wealth, -Mental Health)
Harbinger of Strife: Your birth exacerbates existing family tensions, leading to arguments and blame. The atmosphere is tense. (-Mental Health, -LoveReceiving within family)
Child of Prophecy: Elders whisper you are the one foretold. This brings both reverence and immense, terrifying pressure. (+Luck, +IQ? but -Mental Health from expectation)
The Changeling: There's something... otherworldly about your eyes. People feel unnerved and fascinated by you in equal measure. (+Look? +IQ? but -EQ in connecting normally)
Born with a Veil: Born with a caul (amniotic sac) over your face. Folklore says you have the gift of second sight. (+Luck, +IQ? but possible -Mental Health from visions)
Silent World: You are born deaf. The world you perceive is different from the start, shaping your unique path. (-Skill Points allocated to overcome, but potential for unique strengths later)
Old Soul: Your gaze is wise and knowing beyond minutes. You rarely cry, as if you've seen it all before. (+IQ, +EQ, but -LoveReceiving from those who find it unsettling)
